The squeeze command, sq, is a port of the wedit algorithm for limiting
long intervals of silence within an audio sample.  The duration
of the file is shortened by removing sequences which fall below a
specified loudness level, and which last longer than a specified time.
The thresholds for loudness and time may be set in the edway configuration
file, edway.cfg.  They may also be supplied as a comma separated pair
of numbers as arguments to the sq command.  You may also restrict the
action to a portion of the file by preceding the sq command by one or
a comma separated pair of block addresses.

